oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Game & Fish Office employees with pair of interlocked deer antlers
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Black and white photograph of Miss Barbara Lee and Mrs. McLure of the Game & Fish Office with a pair of interlocked deer antlers. The two employees are posed in front of an animal fur backdrop. The two women are dressed in 1950's era clothing with a skirt and blouse.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:source: RG 82: Tennessee Department of Conservation Photograph Collection, 1937-1976
